<subSubSection id="C30D6559FFA24A17A9F6F87C10D9A687" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA836D2FFA24A17A9F6F87C10D9A687" blockId="3.[151,1436,1956,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA24A17A9F6F87C120FA6DC" bold="true" box="[151,281,1956,1982]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA24A17A840F87D12A8A6DC" box="[289,446,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Female adult</emphasis>
: only extant species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D51FFA24A17ABB9F87D1077A6DC" box="[728,865,1957,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Meloehelea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA24A17ABB9F87D1077A6DC" box="[728,865,1957,1982]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Meloehelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Nearctic Region with a very long slender third palpal segment with PR&gt; 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA24A17AB6DF813110DA687" box="[524,539,1995,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
and about 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA24A17ABFDF81311AFA687" box="[668,697,1995,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="22.0">22</number>
large mandibular teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF68665AFFA54A10A9F6FA741297A76B" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274737/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" targetBox="[151,1430,194,1416]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BA836D2FFA54A10A9F6FA741297A76B" blockId="4.[151,1437,1452,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A9F6FA741209A4A6" bold="true" box="[151,287,1452,1476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D51FFA54A10A8FFFA751706A4A6" authority="Ingram &amp; Macfie." authorityName="Ingram &amp; Macfie." box="[414,1040,1453,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Atrichopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis" subGenus="Meloehelea">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A8FFFA751121A4A6" box="[414,567,1453,1476]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Atrichopogon</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10AB29FA7511DFA4A6" box="[584,713,1453,1476]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Meloehelea</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10ABBAFA75102BA4A6" box="[731,829,1453,1476]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">chilensis</emphasis>
Ingram &amp; Macfie.
</taxonomicName>
A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (ventral view), D—mouthparts (dorsal view), E—antenna, F—wing
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C30D6559FFA54A10A9A4F9EF12DDA602" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA836D2FFA54A10A9A4F9EF11FAA658" blockId="4.[151,1436,1591,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A9A4F9EF1277A733" bold="true" box="[197,353,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Description:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A80BF9E0111EA733" box="[362,520,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Female adult</emphasis>
: Descriptive measurements in 
<tableCitation id="C6950369FFA54A10AA1BF9E010C5A730" box="[890,979,1592,1618]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,151,175]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements of the diagnostic characters of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) species." pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Table 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10AAA2F9E010C5A730" box="[963,979,1592,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10AA83F9EF1733A733" bold="true" box="[994,1061,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Head</emphasis>
: Antenna medium brown, with 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A9F6F98613A3A71A" box="[151,181,1630,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="13.0">13</number>
flagellomeres, flagellomeres 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10AB7BF9861151A71A" box="[538,583,1630,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="4.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="1.0">1–8</number>
disciform, proportions as shown in 
<figureCitation id="132C2A57FFA54A10AA9BF9861756A71A" box="[1018,1088,1630,1656]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,390,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,390,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) ladislavi Tóthová sp. n. A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—mouthparts, D—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (dorsal view), E—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274738/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10AD50F9861756A71A" box="[1073,1088,1630,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B. Mandible well developed, with 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A9B5F95D1208A7FD" box="[212,286,1669,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22</number>
teeth, 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A811F95D128AA7FD" box="[368,412,1669,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
distal teeth very small, 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10ABDDF95D11DDA7FD" box="[700,715,1669,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="9.0">9</number>
at midlength broad. Laciniae with 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10AD11F95D17ACA7FD" box="[1136,1210,1669,1695]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12–13</number>
teeth. Palpus (
<figureCitation id="132C2A57FFA54A10AC0DF95D13B3A7A7" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,390,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,390,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) ladislavi Tóthová sp. n. A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—mouthparts, D—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (dorsal view), E—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274738/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A9F6F97313B3A7A7" box="[151,165,1707,1733]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C) with very long, slender third palpal segment, pit at midlength. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10AAA1F9731708A7A7" bold="true" box="[960,1054,1707,1733]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Thorax</emphasis>
: scutum, scutellum dark brown (
<figureCitation id="132C2A57FFA54A10A9C1F90A13FFA78E" box="[160,233,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,390,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,390,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) ladislavi Tóthová sp. n. A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—mouthparts, D—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (dorsal view), E—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274738/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A9BBF90A13FFA78E" box="[218,233,1746,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A878F90A1248A78E" bold="true" box="[281,350,1746,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="132C2A57FFA54A10A80EF90A12A1A78E" box="[367,439,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,390,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,390,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) ladislavi Tóthová sp. n. A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—mouthparts, D—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (dorsal view), E—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274738/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A8C8F90A12A1A78E" box="[425,439,1746,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E) without pattern of pigmented membrane, with many macrotrichia on the entire membrane. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A840F9201264A670" bold="true" box="[289,370,1784,1810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Halter</emphasis>
: white. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A8B3F920111AA670" bold="true" box="[466,524,1784,1810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Legs</emphasis>
: Light brown; empodia present. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10AAEDF9201710A670" bold="true" box="[908,1030,1784,1810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="132C2A57FFA54A10AD77F921174AA671" box="[1046,1116,1785,1811]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,390,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,390,1658]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female of Atrichopogon (Meloehelea) ladislavi Tóthová sp. n. A—thorax (lateral view), B—head (dorsal view), C—mouthparts, D—terminal abdominal segments and spermathecae (dorsal view), E—wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274738/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10AD2CF921174AA671" box="[1101,1116,1785,1811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D): light brown. 
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10AC41F9201682A670" bold="true" box="[1312,1428,1784,1810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Genitalia</emphasis>
: 
<number id="3DDF24F5FFA54A10A9F6F8F813B0A658" box="[151,166,1824,1850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
equal ovoid spermathecae, each with short neck.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA836D2FFA54A10A9A7F89F12DDA602" blockId="4.[151,1436,1591,2004]" box="[198,459,1862,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B963EAC0FFA54A10A9A7F89F1250A602" box="[198,326,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Male adult</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
